race.comment: SWAG (12) resumes gelded for the Freedman barn and has been switched from the Sydney stable. He's been unlucky not to have broken through in stronger Maidens and presents off two trials with race rider Hutchings aboard. He will be naturally improved and is suited. ARMES (5) found one better at Ipswich on debut when expected to win and was nudged out at the Sunshine Coast following. Thompson rides today for the premier stable and he's a live chance. ODIN'S MOUNT (10) rates similarly on his nose defeat at Eagle Farm bet into $2.7 favouritism. He will also be fitter and will jump and run from an inside barrier. Moor is reunited, replacing Thompson. CROCODILE PIE (6) debuts and his two recent trials here have been sharp. Grahams sticks from those and steers from an inside barrier. The betting will be key.
